**OpenCV :**
           OpenCV (Open source computer vision) is a library of programming functions mainly aimed at real-time computer vision.[1] Originally developed by Intel[2], it was later supported by Willow Garage then Itseez (which was later acquired by Intel[3]). The library is cross-platform and free for use under the open-source BSD license.

**Compiling options(UBUNTU) :**

**Prerequisites :**

1.OpenCV - 3.x or latest version.

2.CMake - 3.x

3.GCC/G++ - 6.x or above

This repository contains Basic image_processing techniques :


1.Display_image_and_video

 This directory contains basic image/video reading and writing api's.

 Implemented code for each operation like image reading , printing the size and channels information of images , videos opening , reading each frame from the videos and as well writing each frame to the recording videos. 

2.Blur

 This directory contains blurring functions

3.Morphological_operation

 This directory contains Morphological operations like erosion and dialtion etc.

4.Threshold

 This directory contains thresholding operatons.



